divs: sighting detailscluster of 6-7 lights (small but bright dots) appeared stationary for about 20 seconds. looking south about 170 degrees and an elevation of about 50 degrees from my backyard near the intersection of mcqueen\elliot. the cluster was about the size of my fist at arms length and seemed to be very high in altitude. the sky was mostly clear with a few wispsy clouds. no air traffic in the immediate area. i was in the swimming pool with my grandkids. we always look up in the sky because there is a fair amount of air traffic because of the proximity to sky harbor airport. i went to get some field glasses and the lights were gone when i returned to the backyard 30 seconds later.
